# AWS CLI & Console Basics

Before you touch any AWS service, get comfortable with two things: the Console for exploration, and the CLI for everything you'll actually automate.

---

## Installing & Configuring the CLI

```bash
# Install (Linux)
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip && sudo ./aws/install

# Verify
aws --version

# Configure default profile
aws configure
# AWS Access Key ID:     AKIA...
# AWS Secret Access Key: xxxxxxxx
# Default region:        ap-south-1       ← set your closest region
# Default output format: json             ← or 'table' for readability
```

Credentials are stored in `~/.aws/credentials`, config in `~/.aws/config`.

