## Named Profiles — Working With Multiple Accounts

You will almost always have more than one AWS account (dev, staging, prod, personal). Named profiles keep them separate.

```bash
# Add a named profile
aws configure --profile prod

# Use a specific profile for any command
aws s3 ls --profile prod
aws ec2 describe-instances --profile dev

# Set a default for the current shell session
export AWS_PROFILE=prod

# Check which identity you are currently using
aws sts get-caller-identity
aws sts get-caller-identity --profile prod
```

Output of `get-caller-identity`:
```json
{
    "UserId": "AIDA...",
    "Account": "123456789012",
    "Arn": "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:user/joon"
}
```

Run this every time before doing something destructive. Saves you from applying prod changes in the wrong account.

