## Useful General Commands

```bash
# Check your account ID
aws sts get-caller-identity --query Account --output text

# List all services you have resources in (rough check)
aws resourcegroupstaggingapi get-resources --output table

# Check service quotas
aws service-quotas list-service-quotas --service-code ec2

# Estimate costs for a running resource type
aws ce get-cost-and-usage \
  --time-period Start=2024-06-01,End=2024-06-30 \
  --granularity MONTHLY \
  --metrics BlendedCost
```

---

## Key Insight for DevOps

Get comfortable with `--query` early. Every time you find yourself copy-pasting an instance ID from the console, ask yourself: "could I get this with a CLI query?" The answer is almost always yes, and a script that fetches IDs dynamically is much more reusable than one with hardcoded values.